  <title>Why is it taking a long time to add elements?</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Why is it taking a long time to add elements?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Notes"><text styleclass="Interface2">Large Model Tips:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Make <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Edit-AutoUpdate" styleclass="VariableName">Auto-Rebuild</link>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">inactive</text><text style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">.</text><text style="font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">&#32;</text><text style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">Then experiment</text>. You can continue to add many elements successfully when rebuild is inactive<text style="font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">.</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> Use </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Edit-AutoUpdate" styleclass="Body Text">Rebuild-Now</link><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text><text style="font-weight:normal; color:#000000;">every 4-5 commands to rebuild.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Machine-Settings" styleclass="Body Text">Number-of-Steps</link> : Use 60 steps, or even less. You do not need many steps as you build the model. You can increase them again to ~120 later. Also, you can increment the model with very small steps with Digital entry of the Master-Machine Angle.</li>
          </list>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Disable <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Visibility-SolidsInMechanisms" styleclass="Body Text">Show Solids in Mechanisms</link> : You do not need to show the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Solids" styleclass="Interface">Solids</link><text styleclass="Interface">&#32;</text>to add elements, to review the kinematics, or to calculate Forces.</li>
          </list>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Application-Settings" anchor="App-Graphics" styleclass="Body Text">Image Quality</link><text styleclass="Body Text"> : If you must show </text><text styleclass="Interface">Solids</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, then experiment with the Image-Quality. Do this when there are many Solids in the model.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-How-to-Edit-Parameters" anchor="Spin-Box" styleclass="Body Text">Spin-Box tool</link><text styleclass="Body Text">. Do </text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">not</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> use the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Spin-Box tool</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. The model re-calculates with each click of the Spin-Box. Use your keyboard to enter new values in each data- box.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="page-break-before:always;"></para>
  </body>
